        "description": "Read NVIC on the L476RG probe"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "**No \u2014 USART2's NVIC interrupt is not enabled.**\n\nReading the live NVIC (attach-without-reset, no state disturbed) on the NUCLEO-L476RG:\n\n- On STM32L4, USART2 is **IRQ 38**, which maps to **`NVIC_ISER1` bit 6**.\n- `NVIC_ISER1` reads **0x00000000** \u2014 bit 6 is clear, so the USART2 interrupt is disabled.\n- In fact every `ISER0\u2013ISER7` register reads 0: **no peripheral interrupts are enabled at all** on the target right now.\n\nThat's consistent with what's flashed \u2014 the descriptor resolves to the **BLINKY** firmware (polling GPIO toggle), which never calls `HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ(USART2_IRQn)` and likely doesn't touch USART2 at all.\n\nIf you expected interrupt-driven UART here, the usual checklist (beyond the NVIC bit) would be `USART2->CR1` UE/RXNEIE/TCIE and the RCC APB1 clock enable \u2014 I can dump `read-peripheral USART USART2` and `RCC` next if you want, but with the BLINKY image loaded the fix is to flash the firmware that actually configures USART2 (e.g. the VCP-ECHO role)."
}